originalText.text: Booked thru SpotHero app and prepaid for ease. $60 all day for Xmas week, as expected for Manhattan garage parking. Prompt service entering and exiting and no issues with the car.

originalText.text: Wish I could give this place zero starts. I drove down into the garage and was completely ignored at first, until a man that works there told me there was no room, angrily walked away, and began honking at me from someone else’s car. I tried to get the attention of the other man that was working there to complain about how rude the other guy was and to try and explain that I was taking my 3 year old somewhere close by that was about to close because I had been looking for street parking for an hour, and before I could get his attention, the other guy started screaming at me in Spanish calling me “puta”. This literally all happened in under 2 minutes. Such an awful experience.

originalText.text: Terrible experience and unprofessional attendants ever!!! They left my car key literally 'outside' of windshield, and didn't tell me anything about this until I left the garage. I was really freaked out when I found the key in between bonnet and wiper. Who would have thought the car key is there?! CRAZY.

originalText.text: Very disrespectful of their customers like they hate you give them any business. I didn't check reviews before reserving a monthly parking there. Felt being bullied there for a whole month. There was one time I notified them 15 mins in advance (they ask you to notify them 30 mins in advance) before picking up the car, they talked to me like I committed a crime. Even though I tried to be nice and went with their rules, they were still very rude to me. I also feel sorry for them having to do a job they hate. Glad that I finally ended my monthly parking there today and moved to elsewhere. Such a relief. I can't take so much pressure and hatred from this garage with what is going on right now in this world. I will definitely get a depression if I park there any longer.
